185
00:09:06,420 --> 00:09:08,150
Those bodies were
never recovered, either.

186
00:09:08,740 --> 00:09:10,170
If there is something out there,

187
00:09:10,310 --> 00:09:11,230
it's picking up its pace.

188
00:09:11,290 --> 00:09:12,750
So we got a lake monster on a binge ?

189
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:15,380
This whole lake monster
theory, it just bugs me.

190
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:16,450
Why ?

191
00:09:16,970 --> 00:09:18,650
Loch Ness, lake Champlain

192
00:09:18,680 --> 00:09:21,150
there are literally hundreds
of eyewitness accounts,

193
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:22,990
but here, almost nothing.

194
00:09:23,300 --> 00:09:24,540
Whatever it is out there,

195
00:09:24,830 --> 00:09:26,130
Noone's living to talk about it.

196
00:09:26,380 --> 00:09:27,590
Wait, Bar,

197
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:29,650
Christopher Bar, where have
I heard that name before ?

198
00:09:29,680 --> 00:09:32,190
Christopher Bar,
the victim in may.

199
00:09:33,790 --> 00:09:35,630
Christopher Bar was
Andrea's husband,

200
00:09:35,910 --> 00:09:37,300
Lucas' father.

201
00:09:37,740 --> 00:09:38,570
Apparently,

202
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:40,560
he took Lucas out swimming.

203
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:43,900
Lucas was on a floating wooden
platform when Chris drowned,

204
00:09:44,180 --> 00:09:45,280
two hours,

205
00:09:45,710 --> 00:09:47,480
before the kid got rescued.

206
00:09:51,050 --> 00:09:53,000
Maybe we have an
eyewitness after all.

207
00:09:53,470 --> 00:09:55,220
No wonder that kid
was so freaked out.

208
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:59,010
Watching one of your parents die
isn't something you just get over.

209
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:02,310
Can we join you ?

210
00:10:06,150 --> 00:10:07,520
I'm here with my son.

211
00:10:10,780 --> 00:10:11,970
Mind if I say hi ?

212
00:10:14,240 --> 00:10:17,530
Tell your friend this whole "jerry maguire"
thing's not gonna work on me.

213
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:19,930
I don't think that's
what this is about.

214
00:10:23,090 --> 00:10:24,190
How's it going ?

215
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:33,520
Oh, I used to
love these things.

216
00:10:39,930 --> 00:10:41,810
So crayons is
more your thing ?

217
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:44,230
That's cool.
Chicks dig artists.

218
00:10:46,590 --> 00:10:47,900
Hey, these are pretty good.

219
00:10:49,420 --> 00:10:51,410
You mind if I sit and
draw with you for a while ?

220
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:53,360
I'm not so bad myself.

221
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:04,290
You know, I'm thinking
you can hear me.

222
00:11:04,820 --> 00:11:06,190
You just don't want to talk.

223
00:11:06,720 --> 00:11:08,820
I don't know exactly
what happened to your dad,

224
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:11,680
but I know it was
something real bad.

225
00:11:15,050 --> 00:11:16,570
I think I know how you feel.

226
00:11:18,930 --> 00:11:21,130
When I was your age,
I saw something.

227
00:11:27,750 --> 00:11:28,890
Anyway . . .

228
00:11:30,820 --> 00:11:33,530
Maybe you don't think
anyone will listen to you.

229
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:35,190
Or, uh...

230
00:11:36,860 --> 00:11:38,090
Or believe you.

231
00:11:38,680 --> 00:11:40,380
I want you to know that I will.

232
00:11:41,730 --> 00:11:43,190
You don't even have to

233
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:45,180
say anything.
You could draw me a picture,

234
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:46,530
about what you saw that day,

235
00:11:46,820 --> 00:11:48,010
with your dad,

236
00:11:49,260 --> 00:11:50,090
on the lake.

237
00:11:54,010 --> 00:11:54,890
Okay,

238
00:11:55,010 --> 00:11:55,960
no problem.

239
00:11:56,410 --> 00:11:57,390
This is for you.

240
00:11:58,470 --> 00:11:59,730
This is my family.

241
00:12:00,980 --> 00:12:02,170
That's my dad.

242
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:03,330
That's...

243
00:12:04,980 --> 00:12:05,970
That's my mom.

244
00:12:06,710 --> 00:12:08,240
That's my geek brother,

245
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:10,250
and that's me.

246
00:12:13,990 --> 00:12:15,620
All right, so I'm
a sucky artist.

247
00:12:16,030 --> 00:12:17,340
I'll see you around, Lucas.

248
00:12:30,030 --> 00:12:32,870
Lucas hasn't said a word,
not even to me,

249
00:12:33,460 --> 00:12:34,520
not since

250
00:12:35,430 --> 00:12:36,950
his dad's accident.

251
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:38,700
Yeah, we heard.

252
00:12:38,970 --> 00:12:39,860
Sorry.

253
00:12:40,940 --> 00:12:42,670
What are the doctors saying ?

254
00:12:42,780 --> 00:12:45,340
That it's a kind of
post-traumatic stress.

255
00:12:45,430 --> 00:12:46,610
That can't be easy

256
00:12:46,760 --> 00:12:47,430
for either of you.

257
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:48,940
We moved in with my dad.

258
00:12:49,870 --> 00:12:51,470
He helps out a lot.

259
00:12:53,390 --> 00:12:54,490
It's just...

260
00:12:56,010 --> 00:12:59,230
when I think about what Lucas
went through, what he saw...

261
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:02,700
Kids are strong.

262
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:05,180
You'd be surprised
what they can deal with.

263
00:13:05,950 --> 00:13:06,970
You know,

264
00:13:07,470 --> 00:13:09,020
he used to have such life.

265
00:13:09,290 --> 00:13:11,590
He was hard to keep up with,
to tell you the truth.

266
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:14,090
Now he just sits there,

267
00:13:14,190 --> 00:13:16,700
drawing those pictures,
playing with those army men.

268
00:13:17,090 --> 00:13:18,180
I just wish.

269
00:13:18,850 --> 00:13:19,900
Hey, sweetie.

270
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:25,950
Thanks.

271
00:13:26,940 --> 00:13:28,030
Thanks, Lucas.

272
